        ],
        [
          "As a mortal you were a soldier.  An officer in the French Army during the first World War, you survived the Battle of Verdun with no physical wounds, but the shell shock changed you forever.  Scattered and lacking focus you wandered the streets of Paris and survived and the meager payments of your pension.  It must have been pre-ordained that the Sabbat found you, because it was only after your embrace that you truly began to live again.  In America you found your salvation in the path of Cathari and the teachings of Judge Inquisitor Cinqo.  He saved you from infernalists who tried to prey on your Weak Will in Montreal and made you his Paladin.  Unfortunately you were only able to serve him for a few years before he asked you to join Michaelangelo's newly formed pack, the Song of Gehenna. As the Abbot you safeguard the pack haven and provide all needs required by the devoutly poor Michaelangelo.  You know that mortals have their uses and have long tried to find your way into the Order of St. Blaise in hopes they can teac you new ways to make use of the mortals."
